<h4><a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-08-05/live-nation-says-fans-want-credit-not-refunds-for-missed-shows?utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_term=200809&amp;utm_campaign=screentime">等疫情过？86% 已购演出门票的消费者选择不退票</a></h4>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1357702" src="https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Live-Nation-Ticket-Refund-Website.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="685" srcset="https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Live-Nation-Ticket-Refund-Website.jpg 1200w, https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Live-Nation-Ticket-Refund-Website-360x206.jpg 360w, https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Live-Nation-Ticket-Refund-Website-768x438.jpg 768w, https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Live-Nation-Ticket-Refund-Website-1024x585.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></p>
<p>《彭博社》消息，全球最大音乐现场活动承办公司 Live Nation 表示，即便近乎所有音乐演出都因疫情延后了，但是 86% 已经购票的消费者都没有选择退票，而是持票等待现场演出的回归。</p>
<p>他们认为这是消费需求被压抑的表现，预计将于 2021 年夏天恢复大型演唱会。在 2020 年第二季度，Live Nation 营收下跌了 98%。</p>
